---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="agentstack — systematic evaluation of agent platforms"
  description="Weekly deep-dives and rigorously-pre-registered third-party evaluations of agent harnesses, memory systems, context repositories, and integration specs. For engineers building agent platforms."
>
  <section class="mb-12">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-3" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
      For engineers building agent platforms
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight mb-6">
      The systematic-evaluation lab for <span style="color: var(--color-accent);">agent systems</span>.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
      Weekly deep-dives on harnesses, memory, context, integrations, and orchestration — plus rigorous, pre-registered third-party evaluations published as replayable canon envelopes. Every finding you can cite in a production design review.
    </p>
  </section>

  <NewsletterSignup />

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 mt-10 tracking-tight">
      How the lab works
    </h2>
    <ol class="space-y-4 max-w-2xl">
      <li>
        <strong>Every eval pre-registers its falsification criteria</strong> — the claim is recorded in canon
        before any data is collected. Post-hoc narrative changes don't happen here.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Raw artifacts are hash-bound.</strong> Transcripts, datasets, and methodology specs are
        referenced by SHA-256 content hash. Post-hoc edits produce new records, not silent overwrites.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Adversarial review before publish.</strong> Every evaluation's methodology is
        pressure-tested against an opposing-perspective agent before the writeup ships.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Sponsored evaluations are cryptographically distinguished.</strong> Paid evals carry a
        <code>Policy.provenance.sponsor</code> attestation in canon. You can always tell.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 mt-10 tracking-tight">
      What we're working on
    </h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 max-w-2xl">
      <li>
        <strong>First lab:</strong> Memory systems comparison — Letta, mem0, MemGPT,
        Claude built-in memory, evaluated on 5 task suites (with one held-out) at
        N≥10 runs per cell. Pre-registration live;
        <a href="/lab/memory-systems-v1/">methodology here</a>. Results publish mid-week-8.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Second lab:</strong> Harness head-to-head on SWE-Bench-Verified, model held constant.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Directory build-out:</strong> harness · memory · orchestration · integration.
        Quality-graded, not star-count-graded.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
